Tailor Your Enablement Programs to Your Company’s Preferred Content System - Developer Preview

Provide a more streamlined connection between your company’s preferred content management system and your Enablement programs. Create custom exercise types that reference content from your own repository or a third-party repository.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in Developer Edition with Sales Cloud. Custom exercise types are available as a developer preview feature.

Who: To add custom exercises to Enablement programs, users must have the View Setup and Configuration permission.

How: Salesforce developers configure the custom items for your Salesforce org using Apex classes and render them on the Salesforce platform through Lightning Web Components.

Enablement admins first add their content to the mapped repository. Then they add a custom exercise to their program from Program Builder and select the content for it.

Sales reps view the referenced content in the flow of the program when they click a custom exercise in the Guidance Center.
title: Tailoring Enablement Programs with Custom Content
